New Records: Nick Castellanos hit a game-winning single in the 11th inning to lead the Phillies to a 3-2 victory over the Braves.
Philadelphia's bullpen pitched five scoreless innings in relief of Aaron Nola.
Aaron Nola recorded his 18th quality start of the season, second-most in the majors behind teammate Zack Wheeler.
Key Match Events: The game went into 11 innings before Nick Castellanos hit a game-winning single.
Carlos Estévez pitched the 10th and 11th innings, retiring all six batters he faced.
Michael Harris II hit a solo home run in the third inning for the Braves.
Pre-Game Insights: The Phillies were looking to increase their NL East lead to seven games.
The Braves were fighting to maintain their position in the National League wild card race.
Manager Rob Thomson emphasized the importance of strong bullpen performance.
Post-Match Reflections: Nick Castellanos joked about his approach to hitting in late innings.
Carlos Estévez received a standing ovation from the sellout crowd after his dominant performance.
Aaron Bummer was charged with an unearned run despite not allowing a hit in two-thirds of an inning.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game had a playoff-like atmosphere with a sellout crowd.
The attendance at Citizens Bank Park was 43,249.
The line was PHI -125 and the over/under was 8.5.
